<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - REMOVE - MAINSHAFT
        ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1302006" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>MAINSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Be careful when removing the mainshaft assembly as the sliding clutch on the end can slip off the
            mainshaft. Reverse gear is also free and can fall off the shaft.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the reverse gear retaining snap ring from the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302052">Figure 52</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302052" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302052" filename="../figg13/G1302052.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the mainshaft reverse gear as far to the rear as possible and remove reverse gear I.D.
                snap ring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the reverse gear forward and against the next gear, engaging the mainshaft sliding
                clutch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302053">Figure 53</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302053" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302053" filename="../figg13/G1302053.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Reverse Gear Forward</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If not removing the upper reverse idler gear assembly, you must remove the upper reverse idler
                        gear assembly shaft and roll the gear to the outside. Refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s13020_HL1302005.xml" xrefid="hl1302005">4.11.</hotlnk>, Reverse idler Gear
                        Assembly, steps 1-4.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a large screwdriver to block the upper countershaft assembly against the case wall (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302054">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302054" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302054" filename="../figg13/G1302054.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Hook Around Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If removing the upper reverse idler gear assembly, refer to
                        <hotlnk document="s13020_HL1302005.xml" xrefid="hl1302005">4.11.</hotlnk>, Reverse idler Gear
                        Assembly, at this time.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position a hook or rope around the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302054">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull the mainshaft to the rear to free the pilot from the input shaft pocket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302054">Figure 54</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>The upper countershaft must be kept forward against the case front wall. Pull the mainshaft
                        rearward and to the right as far as possible.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tilt mainshaft front up and lift assembly from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302055">Figure 55</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302055" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302055" filename="../figg13/G1302055.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Lift Assembly From Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
